latestPosts.caption:
White Lotus 🪷 was the theme I chose for my sister’s engagement — a vision rooted in softness, elegance, and purity. I opted for a soft glam makeup look that reflected my personal style — minimal, graceful, yet impactful.

For my hair, I went with a slightly messy yet effortless style — something that still felt like me.

I paired the look with a simple Jada with gonde /  tassels featuring delicate Lakshmi motifs and of course, the centerpiece of the theme — a white lotus, tying everything together beautifully.

I wore a parrot green soft-silk saree — subtle yet glamorous, traditional yet refreshing, and perfect for my skin tone and the event.
To complement it, I chose a blouse with parrot-detailed threadwork, finished with minimal design and light stonework.

For jewelry, I blended Temple Jewelry with traditional Konkani GSB-style pieces, completed with fine detailing to bring the whole look together.

I carried a subtle creamish-pink potli bag with pearl design — chosen to match the elegance of the outfit and perfectly complement the pearl elements in my jewellery.
